genresAdvancedInfo.name: fo jing
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Fo Jing is a traditional Chinese music genre that originated in the Tang Dynasty (618-907 AD). It features a variety of instruments, including the guqin, pipa, and dizi, and it is characterized by its slow and meditative melodies. The music is often used for relaxation, meditation, and spiritual practices, and it is considered a form of art that reflects the harmony between nature and humanity.
